        <h3><i class="fas fa-microchip"></i> How Deepfakes Work</h3>
        <p>Deepfakes are created using sophisticated artificial intelligence systems known as Generative Adversarial
          Networks (GANs).</p>
        <p>These AI systems consist of two competing neural networks:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Generator:</strong> Creates fake content attempting to be as realistic as possible</li>
          <li><strong>Discriminator:</strong> Tries to detect whether the content is real or fake</li>
          <li><strong>Learning Loop:</strong> Both networks improve over time, resulting in increasingly convincing
            fakes</li>
          <li><strong>Training Data:</strong> Uses thousands of images/videos to learn facial expressions and movements
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>As these networks compete, the generator becomes better at producing realistic fakes that are increasingly
          difficult to detect with the naked eye.</p>
      </div>

